WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.730 --> 00:00:05.210
How to Live on a Budget.

00:00:05.210 --> 00:00:10.620
They don’t call it minimum wage for nothing
... How’s a guy supposed to get ahead, breaking

00:00:10.620 --> 00:00:14.430
his back 24-7, when all it gets you is chicken
scratch?

00:00:14.430 --> 00:00:17.930
My friend, you need a budget.

00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:28.180
You will need Discipline Ability to add, subtract,
multiply, and divide and bank or credit union.

00:00:28.180 --> 00:00:29.320
Step 1.

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:36.190
Add up all your income.

00:00:36.190 --> 00:00:37.540
Step 2.

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:40.350
Divide the total by the number of months it
took you to earn it.

00:00:40.350 --> 00:00:45.020
The result is your monthly income.

00:00:45.020 --> 00:00:46.120
Step 3.

00:00:46.120 --> 00:00:57.100
Add up your essential monthly expenses, like
food, rent, transportation, and personal necessities.

00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:58.100
Step 4.

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:06.250
Next add up your nonessential monthly spending.

00:01:06.250 --> 00:01:07.310
Step 5.

00:01:07.310 --> 00:01:12.550
Now add up your expenses, and pray the total
is lower than your monthly income.

00:01:12.550 --> 00:01:19.430
If your expenses exceed your income, you’ll
need to cut back on nonessential items.

00:01:19.430 --> 00:01:20.440
Step 6.

00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:22.760
Once your numbers are set, stick to them!

00:01:22.760 --> 00:01:26.640
Discipline is the key to living on a budget.

00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:31.420
Try to set aside a small portion of your income
on a regular basis—make sure to deposit

00:01:31.420 --> 00:01:35.290
it in a secure savings institution.

00:01:35.290 --> 00:01:36.350
Step 7.

00:01:36.350 --> 00:01:40.650
Take public transportation, or carpool with
friends to save on gas.

00:01:40.650 --> 00:01:45.150
Walking is free, and it’s great exercise!

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:46.150
Step 8.

00:01:46.150 --> 00:01:47.280
Be frugal.

00:01:47.280 --> 00:01:50.260
Stop buying brand name clothes and fancy foods.

00:01:50.260 --> 00:01:51.470
Stop drinking lattes.

00:01:51.470 --> 00:01:55.060
Don’t order takeout.

00:01:55.060 --> 00:01:59.230
Instead of buying napkins, wipe your mouth
on your sleeve.

00:01:59.230 --> 00:02:00.230
Step 9.

00:02:00.230 --> 00:02:02.220
Buy anything you can secondhand.

00:02:02.220 --> 00:02:07.270
Thrift stores often sell household goods and
perfectly good used clothing.

00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:18.680
Did you know According to the Department of
Education, more than 80% of undergrads have

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:24.410
at least one credit card, and nearly 50% have
four or more.

